## WHAT I DID

- **Audited** the existing repo: Auth & Identity has already shipped the sign-up form, mode switcher, verify hub, and avatar uploader inside their owned `/app/(auth)/` segment; Core API has frozen the profiles contract at `app/api/profiles/CONTRACT.md`.
- **Built the public landing page** at `app/page.tsx` (+ `app/page.module.css`) — mobile-first, signed-in users redirect to `/verify`, with clear CTAs into the Auth-owned sign-up and login flows and a "How it works" panel grounded in the core product rules.
- **Built the companion profile setup screen** at `app/profile/page.tsx` + `app/profile/CompanionProfileSetup.tsx` + `app/profile/styles.module.css`:
  - Server-component gate: redirects unauthed → `/login`, missing mirror row → `/verify`, non-companion → `/mode`.
  - Client component fetches `GET /api/profiles/me` and renders **loading skeleton**, **404-as-empty-state** (defaults that satisfy the API CHECK constraints), **error with retry**, and **populated edit form**.
  - Fields: headline, bio_long, rate (dollars ↔ cents conversion), currency, meal types (lunch/dinner checkboxes), service area lat/lng with an opt-in "use my current location" button (respects browser permission prompt — core product rule on explicit location consent), service radius (km ↔ meters).
  - Client-side validation mirrors the Zod bounds in `validators.ts` so the user gets immediate field errors before round-tripping.
  - Saves via `PUT /api/profiles/me`; distinguishes 201 (created) vs 200 (updated) in the success banner.
  - **Verification banner** reads `verification_status` and shows verified/pending/rejected/unverified pills (with a link to `/verify` — Auth's flow). It never writes `verification_status` (forbidden by the contract).
  - **Weekly availability editor**: lists existing windows, supports add (`POST`) with day/start/end/meal-type/timezone (defaults to browser IANA tz) and per-row delete (`DELETE /api/profiles/me/availability/[id]`). Disabled until the profile exists, with a notice explaining the dependency on profile-row existence (matches the 409 surface from the API).
- **Shared components** (`/components/`): `Spinner.tsx` (accessible inline loading indicator) and `StatusMessage.tsx` (tone-coded banner).
- **Wired to Auth session** via the existing `AuthProvider` / `useAuth()` (post-mount session expiry surfaces a friendly error state).
- **Verified**: `tsc --noEmit` shows zero new errors from my files; prettier passes on all new files; vitest passes; Next.js production compile step succeeds (only the pre-existing `lib/supabase/server.ts` post-compile typecheck fails, see manual checkpoints).
- Committed as `phase-1(frontend): landing page + companion profile setup screen`.

## WHAT I COULD NOT DO

- **Did not rebuild the sign-up / mode-select form UI itself**: Auth & Identity already shipped it inside `/app/(auth)/sign-up/` and `/app/(auth)/mode/`, both of which are explicitly owned by Auth & Identity in CLAUDE.md's repository structure. Modifying those files would be an out-of-scope edit. The landing page now routes users into the existing Auth-owned flow.
- **No map preview / picker** on service area: `/lib/maps` is empty (Integrations agent hasn't published the Maps module yet), so I built numeric lat/lng + geolocation-API helper instead. Will swap in a map UI in a later phase once `/lib/maps` lands.
- **No avatar upload widget on `/profile`**: avatar upload is owned by Auth & Identity (`lib/auth/storage.ts#uploadAvatar`, surfaced on `/verify`). The profile setup screen links to `/verify` for that. The Core API photo endpoint (`PUT /api/profiles/me/photo`) is for re-pointing to an *already uploaded* key — left for a later iteration once we have a photo gallery UX.
- **Could not run `npm run lint`**: ESLint 8.57 + Next 16 + this repo's `.eslintrc.json` crashes on a circular structure (`property 'react' closes the circle`) — pre-existing, not something my code introduced.
- **Could not finish `npm run build`**: pre-existing typecheck error on `lib/supabase/server.ts:26` (`cookies()` returns `Promise<ReadonlyRequestCookies>` under Next 16). Foundations-scope.

## INTERFACES PUBLISHED

Frontend doesn't expose APIs for other agents to consume, but I'm establishing these reusable surfaces inside Frontend-owned space:

- `@/components/Spinner` — `<Spinner size?={number} label?={string} />`. Accessible inline loading indicator that inherits `currentColor`.
- `@/components/StatusMessage` — `<StatusMessage tone="error" | "notice" | "success" role?={'alert'|'status'}>...</StatusMessage>`. Shared banner; the auth segment already has a CSS-module-scoped equivalent that intentionally stays separate.
- **`/profile`** route: the canonical place a companion edits their profile and availability. Internally consumes only the frozen `app/api/profiles/CONTRACT.md` contract — no new wire contract introduced.
- **`/` (root)**: public landing with `/sign-up` and `/login` entry points (existing Auth & Identity routes).

